Hey everyone it’s my Birthday 🥳🎂🎁🎉

The way God has blessed me & this little family of mine is nothing short of mind blowing. 
Here’s to many more years of good health, wealth, peace, love & happiness. 💫

We will never be those people who pretend on these squares. Throughout the year I’ve (Abigail) been very open that it’s been one heck of a challenging year, what emotion have I not felt. 

However while it’s ok to feel the feelings, as a family we will ALWAYS be thankful for what we have and celebrate every single win, big or small! This year we said more activities and experiences with the kids and for us, as simple as it may seem,that’s a win! 

While we’ll always have some big goals and dreams we’re really learning to truly embrace and appreciate the little things and simple moments. 

We pray this near year God grants you all your hearts desires, may you have peace and sound mind, may you find healing wherever you may need it and may you feel love always. May you be congratulated!! 🎉

Thank you for rolling with The Amp’s 🤎

First post of 2023 and we’re starting as we mean to go! We have a few words for this year and they are ORGANISE & ROUTINE!!
I (Abigail) spent way too long ignoring the importance of having some sort of order and thinking I can just keep it in my head, but in reality I was stressing myself out. From day to day tasks,  the kids, to work and as a family, we started writing everything down and it’s helped massively 

What do we use?
📝A whiteboard calender in the kitchen where we write every event, appointment, deadline etc! ANYTHING happening for that month goes there 
📝A study plan for the kids so we know we’re covering  some additional  areas of learning daily. We’re using a mix of resources including some from @twinklresources which we’ve found so helpful. 
📝Our vision board has things relating to our bigger goals and aspirations. We have images, quotes, scriptures anything that’ll keep is inspired 
📝A real life kanban board using post-it notes to track what is To Do, In Progress and Done 
📝A @paper.penie diary to keep things on the go 

I’m a visual person so having all these things where I can literally see them day to day is a huge help and I’m already feeling more productive, less overwhelmed and less anxious. 

There’s so many ways to get things in order. 
Here’s to a productive & successful 2023!

I saw a quote that said “There are no seven wonders in the world in the eyes of children; there are seven million”

I’m loving this age (most days 😂)I almost feel like I’m reliving my childhood with them. They’ve given me new energy for adventure & I’m discovering so many wonders through their eyes, It’s so fascinating. 

Somedays I’m like aww don’t grow up, but I’m sure there’s only more great moments to come. 
So while they’re little I’m going to savour every moment ❤️
Have a great week Instafam

It’s one of the best months of the year because it means it’s almost another trip around the sun, not just my birthday but our anniversary too. As I celebrate my birthday month, I'm grateful for the lessons learned the past year! 

One of the biggest takeaways? A loud reminder not to take things personally, even if they seem that way. Why? Because we really never know what someone’s going through, so I’ll extend the same grace to others that I’d like to receive. We’re all fighting some sort of battle that nobody may know about or even understand! Everything isn’t black and white, there are indeed many grey areas and we need to consider that. 

This time last year my mental health took a massive nose dive to a place it had never been before, getting out of bed was just long!, confidence in myself, my abilities, my plans, you name it was out of the window! 
However I’m welcoming the new month with so much gratitude! I still have my moments but gosh I’m not where I was mentally a year ago and for that I’m thankful, it can only get better. 

Happy New Month Instafam

What a difference a year makes. Pretty much this time last year I got some news that wasn’t in line with my plans. Fast forward to today, while i’ve learnt I’m not at the desired outcome my thought process, my reasoning, my outlook and my solution to it has had a total shift. It’s having almost zero impact now, simply because I’ve really been able to channel my thoughts and I love that! 

I don’t know if anyone needs this this morning but I pray that you find a new perspective to get through whatever may look difficult, seems like there’s no end in sight or weighing down. 

Hope you all had an amazing weekend. Here’s to a great week of breakthroughs instafam. 🤎

We hired a bus which was a great idea as we’re a large group and it’s about 2 hours out of Accra! 🚎

When you get there you need to hop a boat to go across to Treasure island itself.🚤

As we were leaving some people were pulling up, so I assume you can enjoy it in the evening too!

Been a while since we did a little Eden update. We can’t quite believe the end of the school year is fast approaching. He’s settled in so well in school we honestly couldn’t have wished for a better environment, it’s exactly what we prayed for. He’s made huge progress in so many areas and we’re coming along one word and short sentences at a time lol. 

One Monday I (Abigail) spoke with a sister who said you have no idea how you touch people when you’re open about certain things. She said she was going through some challenges with her son so bad that she didn’t want to be here anymore. She saw a post I shared and it reminded her she’s not alone and for that alone, I’ll always do these updates and I actually plan to do a lot more around SEN. 

So while there’s progress overall, what we won’t do is act like there aren’t challenging days, while they’re not frequent we will always be transparent. On the last week of term I picked Eden up from school and his teacher told me he was upset and asked if I could come in the class. I was met with a boy having the biggest meltdown I have ever witnessed because he wanted to take home a particular toy. What felt like hours passed, the school was empty it was just his teachers and I, nothing was working. Eventually I had to call David to come and meet me and when he arrived I had a meltdown of my own lol and he asked why are you crying. 

I was thinking why is this guy asking me such a question! We got home, Eden was jolly like he didn’t try and snatch my wig and David said of course it’s upsetting but if you spend too much time worrying or getting upset through the process it’ll end up blinding you from all the amazing things that’s happening and milestones that have been reached and he’s right. 

While Eden is on a journey of development there has been so much progress which we must not lose sight of. I’m not sure if someone needs to read this today or if you come across this post another day. Be proud, look back and think of the things you were praying and wishing for that they’ve now been able to do, it can only get better and it will 🤎
May this new month bring great miracles, new visions, greater blessings and beautiful memories just like this for you and your loved ones. 🤎

Before Eden started school the fear of the unknown would literally make me burst into tears. Over this year I’ve heard mixed reviews and some unfortunate stories of experiences in other schools which is sad. I can only thank God that has not been our story. Rather, school has been a place that Eden literally runs to in the morning, a place that honestly gives us peace of mind. 

At his end of year review his teacher mentioned one student in particular connects with him so well and always looks out for him. This lovely little girl happens to be our neighbour and their teacher had no idea. I had no idea she was doing this, her parents had no idea either when I told them. Her mum said she always talks about Eden being kind to her and she also helps him🥹 Her parents were so proud of her, let’s strive to raise kind humans. To think I was worried about other kids, he is surrounded by some lovely classmates. 

Where do I even begin with the teachers and all the resources in the school, their dedication to make it inclusive for all kids! 

There has not been a single day we worried about sending him to school and we are so thankful. I pray all families can have the experience we’ve had, and long may it last. 

This is just the first page of what will be such a beautiful story. We so proud of Eden

Who remembers our jar of good things? So many events can happen in a year and typically the negatives always hit harder! We made this jar to keep a note of the positives, both big and small. 
Looking through the various wins we’ve had this year, some we even forgot, has been encouraging. From work, business to the kids, looking through these notes we’re reminded God truly has been faithful. 
We are hopeful, expectant and ready for the year ahead. To this little community here, we cannot end the year without saying thank you for riding with us. 
Here’s to ushering in a year blessings, joy and Gods unmerited favour 🫶🏾

At the start of the year we like to take some time out to go over our plans for the year!

We started off by changing our environment for the weekend! We know ourselves and there’s too many distractions at home for this to work. 

We take a look at the main pillars that’ll shape the year, and take time to break down all the things that make up that pillar. 

It could be a big plan like buying a house or smaller ones like booking a lesson for the kids, without even thinking about it, everything has a process and system so it makes sense for us to leave no stone unturned and write them all down. 

Now this doesn’t mean everything is going to go exactly as planned but it’s a great guide and the truth is it’s easier to execute things with some sort of system in place.

Is this something you would or currently do in your home?
